SAY: Welcome to today's tutorial on building a REST API with Node.js
SAY: We'll start by setting up our project directory and installing dependencies

ACTION: Open your terminal application

COMMAND: mkdir my-api && cd my-api

COMMAND: npm init -y

SAY: Now let's install Express, our web framework of choice

COMMAND: npm install express

SAY: Let's create our main application file

ACTION: Create a new file called index.js

SAY: We'll set up a basic Express server with a hello world endpoint
SAY: Notice how we import Express and create an app instance

ACTION: Switch to browser and open localhost:3000

COMMAND: node index.js

SAY: And there we have it - our API is running!
SAY: In the next section, we'll add database connectivity
